Size is fixed internally.
Once the arraylist is filled to a specific portion a new arraylist of double the size is created automatically
and the elements are copied to it. Time complexity for this is O(1)

## methods
   list.add(int val); //to add data in ArrayList
   list.get(int index); //to get value at index
   list.contains(int n); //gives true or false.
   list.set(int index,int newValue); //changes the value at a particular index.
   list.remove(int index); //removes the value at particular index.
   list.get(int index); //prints the value at particular index.
   list.size(); //gives size of the list
   Collections.sort(list); // for sorting list

Wrapper class na ho to kuch bhi add kar skte ho.
ArrayList l = new ArrayList();